ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Percentage of time subject rated a face as positive over all trials
Percentage of time subject rated a face as neutral over all trials
Percentage of time subject rated a face as negative over all trials
Percentage of time subject did not make a response over all trials
Reaction time of subject when rating a face as positive
Reaction time of subject when rating a face as neutral
Reaction time of subject when rating a face as negative
Percentage of time subject recognized a new positive face as new, regardless of confidence rating of subject on answer (i.e. disregarding "maybe" "probably" "sure" new)
Percentage of time subject recognized a old positive face as old regardless of confidence rating of subject on answer (i.e. disregarding "maybe" "probably" "sure" old)
Percentage of time subject recognized a new neutral face as new regardless of confidence rating of subject on answer (i.e. disregarding "maybe" "probably" "sure" new)
Percentage of time subject recognized a old neutral face as old regardless of confidence rating of subject on answer (i.e. disregarding "maybe" "probably" "sure" old)
Percentage of time subject recognized a new negative face as new regardless of confidence rating of subject on answer (i.e. disregarding "maybe" "probably" "sure" new)
Percentage of time subject recognized a old negative face as old regardless of confidence rating of subject on answer (i.e. disregarding "maybe" "probably" "sure" old)
Reaction time of subject when rating whether a positive face as new or old
Reaction time of subject when rating whether a neutral face as new or old
Reaction time of subject when rating whether a negative face as new or old
